  "title_full": "AN ACT ESTABLISHING THE RIGHTS AND WELFARE OF PLATFORM WORKERS, ENSURING FAIR COMPENSATION, SOCIAL PROTECTION, AND MECHANISMS FOR ACCOUNTABILITY AND COLLECTIVE REPRESENTATION, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES",
  "title_short": "",
  "abstract": "Defines several terms among others:  Platform Worker refers to any individual who performs labor or services through a digital platform, regardless of employment status, including but not limited to delivery personnel, ride-hailing drivers, online freelance workers, virtual assistants, and creative service providers; Digital Platform refers to any internet-based application or website that mediates and facilitates the matching of demand for and supply of labor or services between a client or consumer and a platform worker. Proposes several provisions among others as follows: presumption of employment relationship; rights and entitlements (social protection and welfare benefits such as SSS, PhilHealth, Pag-IBIG, and accidental insurance); right to information and algorithmic transparency; right to organize and collective bargaining; protection against unjust deactivation; etc.",
